data.title: Burnet County, Texas Population 2024
data.text:
Burnet County, Texas 's estimated 2024 population is 55,415 with a growth rate of 2.64% in the past year according to the most recent United States census data. Burnet County, Texas is the 66th largest county in Texas. The 2010 population was 42,760 and has seen a growth of 29.6% since that time.

Poverty in Burnet County, Texas

The race most likely to be in poverty in Burnet County, Texas is Islander , with 60% below the poverty level.

The race least likely to be in poverty in Burnet County, Texas is Asian , with 1.92% below the poverty level.

The poverty rate among those that worked full-time for the past 12 months was 2.2% . Among those working part-time, it was 7.15% , and for those that did not work, the poverty rate was 12.48% .
